.TH "LIGHTNING-FEE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-fee \- per-channel fee policy (FEAT-188)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning fee
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning fee — per-channel fee policy (FEAT-188).

Wraps clightning's `setchannel` + `listchannels`. Fees are
what makes a routing node profitable; see BOLT-7
§channel_update for the wire format.

Subcommands:
  get [<channel-id>]                    show base+ppm
  set <channel-id> <base-msat> <ppm>    update
  policy <name>                         apply named policy
                                         (flat | lsp-style | match-peer)
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning fee <subcommand>

   get [<channel-id>]                    TSV of base / ppm per channel
   set <channel-id> <base-msat> <ppm>    update one channel
   policy <name>                         apply a named policy across all:
                                          - flat       (1000 msat + 1 ppm)
                                          - lsp-style  (0   msat + 250 ppm)
                                          - match-peer (copy peer's fees)
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
